items.name: Reinhardt (Overwatch) LORA
items.description:
My eighth Overwatch LORA. 2 versions - without LoCon, and experimental one with, example prompts\seeds same between versions. Focused on original appearance.

  • Face - reinhardt, old man, white hair, scar across eye, beard

  • Armor - power armor, helmet, lion shield

  • Weapon - warhammer, holding hammer

  • Accessories - lion shield, animal print

Checked strength range is 0.7-0.9, but feel free to experiment. Eyes are a bit finicky cause of the scar, and because they rather small by themselves.

Can't tell for sure if there's noticeable enough difference in quality with LoCon version to switch, so let me know if there's any big differences for you. I probably haven't done the best possible job with implementing it, so I will keep experimenting with it for a few more LORA's.

If you liked my work, you can donate here.

Review and comment with your experiences, I would appreciate whatever feedback you can provide in order to continue improving my technique.

Trained on Anything V4.5 with anime.vae.pt and CLIP Skip 2.

Samples are 512x768, without HighRes.fix (mostly), using OrangeCocoa 50/50 Mix , with OrangeMix VAE, and using EasyNegative embedding, CLIP Skip 2. Inpaint examples are txt2img with 1 single inpaint done on face (I will comment on exceptions).

items.description:
中文版在下面

(use LoCon)

Recommended resolution: 768x768

Recommended vae: orangemix, anyting-v4.0, anyhentai_18

 

  • If any other LoRA is not used, the suggested weight of this Lora is about: 0.55-0.75.

  • tag of Regularization(optional):mamimi

  • Lower weight gets clearer picture, which may be similar to the early artstyle of Mamimi?

  • In the case of low resolution, the rendered image may be blurred, but it can be improved by using any upscale function in stable diffusion to fix it like high res fix or ultimate sd upscaler. Denoising recommends about 0.3-0.4.

And after improving the resolution the art style is still kind similar to Mamimi.

 

****Detailed weight recommendation of this LoRA:****

  • Only this LORA used and using Additional Networks (LoRA): 0.65-0.75

  • Only this LORA used and using in prompt: 0.65-0.75

 

  • Using with another single Lora: 0.65-0.75. If there have little blur, can repair it in High res fix.

  • Using with other multiple Lora: 0.55-0.75. If there have little blur, can repair it in High res fix.

 

When using the "Composable LoRA" and "Latent couple" plug-ins to generate multiplayer characters in the scene:

  • Using Additional Networks (LoRA): 0.5-0.65. If using this LoRA results in the loss of some characters features, you can appropriately lower the weight of this LoRA or increase the weight of the character LoRA

  • Using in prompt: 0.65-0.75

Unfortunately, I don't know how to train body position, if I know how to do it, I want to try to train some bestiality and other body position painted by Mamimi.

Mamimi大佬的画风，第一版先凑合用。

用anything4.5训练的LoRA

只训练了250多张图片（加上正则化也才290多张），20epoch, 每张图片10step，然后用的Lion优化。 有没有大佬教一下哪种参数训练画风最好，感谢。

推荐分辨率：768x768

推荐vae：orangemix, anyting-v4.0, anyhentai_18

  • 如果不用任何其他LoRA，此lora的权重建议价是0.55-0.75左右。

  • 正则化tag(可选）：mamimi

  • 权重低的话可以保持比较清晰的画面，可能类似mamimi作者早期画风？

  • 分辨率低的情况下，渲染出来的图可能会糊，但可以用高清修复来提高清晰度或者ultimate sd upscaler啥的，提高清晰度后的画风还是很像mamimi大佬的。denoising推荐0.3-0.4左右

****这个LoRA的详细权重推荐:****

  • 单独使用/Additional Networks (LoRA)：0.65-0.75

  • 单独使用/直接在prompt：0.65-0.75

  • 与单个其他lora配合的权重：0.65-0.75，如果模糊，跑一边高清修复就行了

  • 如果用的是Additional Networks (LoRA)：这个lora的权重建议价是0.5-0.65. 如果开启这个lora导致一些人物lora的特征丢失，那么可以适当把此lora权重调低，或把人物lora的权重弄高一点

  • 如果是直接再prompt里使用：这个lora的权重建议价是0.65-0.75左右.

可惜不知道怎么训练体位，要不然想试试训练出Mamimi大佬画的一些兽X之类的动作。

items.name: Phanes
items.description:
TL:DR

It's a Style LoRA which attempts to focus on a slightly more realistic style, but doesnt quite manage to do that, instead going for a unique style that looks, well Unique.

Does it have preferred settings?

Test it out for yourself, I've gotten decent results with most settings, but generally i'd avice going for:

  1. Just 1 Character at a time (1girl, solo)

  2. A median CFG value (4-20),

  3. Sticking between 0.4 ~ 0.8 LoRA strength.

  4. Steps don't matter too much unless you are using an ancestral Sampler (In my experience)

Model was Trained on Anything V4.5 Pruned Safetensor

Phanes:

Phanes or Protogonus (lit. 'first-born') was the mystic primeval deity of procreation and the generation of new life in Greek Mythology.

This admittedly borderline Cliché name (for something that technically doesnt even create something, but rather just assists in it), was chose without any specific reason, other than me thinking it sounds cool, and there being (so far) no conflicting tags or other models/LoRA's named like that.

This LoRA comes in:

V1: Slightly Overcooked (maybe) which was trained at around 16.8k steps (long story short, i thought epochs would Split/Divide the step count, not Multiply it), still turned out good.

V1.1: Slightly less cooked at 1.6k steps, also slightly more Stable than V1 at higher CFG Values (at least from my testing).

V2: Same as V1.1, only trained with a higher Image Pool size, and slightly different settings, most notably full FP16.

O.K. but what was it trained on?

V1&V1.1: A set of 56 Handpicked Danbooru Images which come from diffrent artists, but have a similar artstyle.

V2: The original 56 + 54 Extra Images.

All Images were Autotagged by Toriatos WD14-Tagger in Automatic1111's Web-UI, and manually cleaned up.

The LoRA itself was trained using Bmaltais Kohya_ss GUI

items.name: Sakimi Mix
items.description:
Early Version

So I decided to train my own checkpoint with a twist - I added Sakimi-chan's artstyle to the mix and combined it with other checkpoints through fine-tuning. But let's be real, this checkpoint is like a toddler - it's still in its early stages and may not always behave the way you want. So be warned, the style it releases may surprise you!

How To Use?

Alright, here's the deal - to use this checkpoint, you gotta type in the magic words: "sakimi mix" into your prompt. Trust me, it's mandatory, 'cause that's the trigger word that brings this checkpoint to life. Then, generate your image and transfer it to img2img to give it that extra oomph and upscale it to your heart's content. This nifty trick can help iron out any pesky defects in your image, making it look sleek and stunning. Happy creating!

v2.1 & v2.0

Other versions

A LoRA (Hadamard Product) based on 966 Shiny Colors cards, recognizing the 26 characters to varying degrees.

Resumed from deresute-v1.3-epoch16 by accident instead of training from scratch, retaining surprisingly much of the knowledge of Cinderella Girls characters. This suggests that it's likely the model's capacity is nowhere close to being reached.

This also serves as a demo of an extremely inefficient style transfer method: train the characters, and then train on lots of unrelated styled images.

  • 996 Shiny Colors cards collected from シャニマスDB

items.name: Nico Robin (One Piece) Pre and Post Timeskip LoRA
items.description:
Nico Robin (One Piece) LoRA (pre and post timeskip)

CHECK BOTH VERSIONS

Pre Timeskip: https://civitai.com/models/18008?modelVersionId=21286
Post Timeskip: https://civitai.com/models/18008?modelVersionId=21283

Also check your filter settings as default ones censor "sexy outfits"

Making models can be expensive. Do you like what I do? Consider supporting me on Patreon 🅿️ or feel free to buy me a coffee ☕

Like the Nami LoRA, this wasn't easy. Every version of Robin is extremely detailed, with precise drawings on her outfit, plus she changes completely after the timeskip and, as it usually happens with One Piece characters, she doesn't always wear the same thing (and the available data is inconsistent because of that).

Again, I had to accept some compromise. Like with Nami, I had to make two LoRA's instead of one. Second I needed to focus on getting her main outfit right, while still keeping the flexibility to be able to use this LoRA with custom outfits and styles.

The main outfits are almost always right, and both versions I made (pre and post timeskip) should be fine to use at weight 1, at least on the models I tested.

Triggers with nico robin for better accuracy. Also use short hair in pre timeskip version. Some of the examples are also using my Wano Style LoRA and my Eiichiro Oda LoRA.

Please enjoy, and remember that your LoRA filename will be different from the one used in the examples.

How to use LoRA's in auto1111:

  • Update webui (use git pull like here or redownload it)

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoRA like in this video

  • Make sure to change the weight according to the instructions (by default it's :1)

«Нива» (известна под названиями ВАЗ-2121 «Ни́ва», Lada Niva, LADA 4x4 и LADA Niva Legend) — советский и российский автомобиль повышенной проходимости — внедорожник малого класса с несущим кузовом и постоянным полным приводом.

Серийно производится с 5 апреля 1977 года (до 2006 года продавался под именем ВАЗ-2121 «Ни́ва» на внутреннем рынке, и как Lada Niva на экспортных рынках[2][3], с 2006 по 2021 годы под именем LADA 4x4, с 2021 года — LADA Niva Legend).

Британский исследователь советского автомобилестроения Энди Томпсон считает «Ниву» прямым предком класса компактных кроссоверов, на который ориентировались создатели автомобиля Suzuki Vitara[4]. Некоторыми экспертами называется лучшим автомобилем в истории Волжского автозавода[5], является самой успешной экспортной моделью ВАЗа за всю историю[6].

items.name: CDMan
items.description:
Model to make "cross dressing" men.

Many SD models seem to have a strong bias regarding "man" and "woman," including things like facial features, body shape and clothing. If you try to mix what the model considers to be a "man" face and body with "female" clothing, the result is often a "feminization" of the face and body or a "masculinization" of the clothing. This LoRA is an attempt to allow the creation of images of a traditional "man" face and body with traditional "female" clothing. No special trigger words, but all images were tagged with "man" so include it or some member of the "man" class for best results. It is definitely not perfect, but worth a try if you are interested.
